<article id="post-1020" class="post-1020 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-family category-general tag-moving">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/a-moving-birthday/" rel="bookmark">A Moving Birthday</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>When we started planning this crazy little excursion to Costa Rica oh-so-many months ago, there was always the need for me to leave in advance of my family, and then come back to get them. The logistics of making everything happen were basically impossible to handle any other way. That month away wasn&#8217;t easy, which you already know. Issues of living in Costa Rica aside, the reality of being that far from my family was far more harsh than I had ever imagined.<br />
Needless to say, when I arrived last night, I was overjoyed to see that Mi Pequeña Niña (I think I&#8217;m going to use &#8220;MI Niñita&#8221; from now on, by the way &#8212; that seems to be the prefered version of &#8220;little girl&#8221;) recognised me. You have no idea how good that felt.<br />
Today was packing day. And also my 36th birthday.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/a-moving-birthday/#more-1020" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;A Moving Birthday&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/a-moving-birthday/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-07-16T22:32:29-06:00">16 July 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/family/" rel="category tag">Family</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/moving/" rel="tag">moving</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/a-moving-birthday/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on A Moving Birthday</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-1020 -->

<article id="post-1019" class="post-1019 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general tag-alajuela tag-automobiles">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/buying-a-car-in-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark">Buying a car in Costa Rica</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>We tried to survive without cars. Really. We took taxis everywhere, and suffered due to the language barrier and an unfamiliar taxi system. (We&#8217;ve been unable to get taxis when we need them &#8212; baffling, when you see them driving around &#8212; and gouged when meters have been turned on.) We could try the bus system, but so far we&#8217;ve been utterly unable to understand them. We don&#8217;t know what the routes or schedules are.<br />
So we went to renting a car &#8212; an infinitely better improvement, as we can go where we need to go when we want to. And if we feel the urge to take a detour to explore a bit, it&#8217;s not a problem. But rental cars aren&#8217;t cheap &#8212; it costs a few hundred dollars a week.<br />
The natural conclusion, and something we&#8217;d planned all along, is to buy a car. But it&#8217;s harder than it sounds.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/buying-a-car-in-costa-rica/#more-1019" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Buying a car in Costa Rica&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/buying-a-car-in-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-07-14T10:27:45-06:00">14 July 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/alajuela/" rel="tag">alajuela</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/automobiles/" rel="tag">automobiles</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/07/buying-a-car-in-costa-rica/#comments">4 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Buying a car in Costa Rica</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
