<article id="post-982" class="post-982 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-family category-general tag-cats tag-immigration tag-pets">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/bringing-my-cat-into-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark">Bringing my cat into Costa Rica</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>We&#8217;re bringing Asia with us. Not the continent; <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/sowrey/2142575972/in/set-72157603438169851/">she&#8217;s our cat</a>. We don&#8217;t want to part with her. She&#8217;s a wonderful pet and truly part of the family. She was our first baby before Mi Niña Pequeña came along. Giving her up is just not an option.<br />
Getting her through the border is the trouble. Mostly because there is no de facto source of information on how this is done properly. What I have found is confusing and very contradictory. For someone who is going to be spending 12 hours with an annoyed kitteh (LOLCat spelling) &#8212; she might be stuck in that cage the entire time &#8212; I need to know that getting into the country isn&#8217;t going to kill her.<br />
Or me.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/bringing-my-cat-into-costa-rica/#more-982" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Bringing my cat into Costa Rica&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/bringing-my-cat-into-costa-rica/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-06-03T11:35:47-06:00">3 June 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/family/" rel="category tag">Family</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/cats/" rel="tag">cats</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/immigration/" rel="tag">immigration</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/pets/" rel="tag">pets</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/bringing-my-cat-into-costa-rica/#comments">3 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Bringing my cat into Costa Rica</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
